<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="245" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,259,430]" pageId="19" pageNumber="245">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,331,357]" pageId="19" pageNumber="245">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[734,870,331,358]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="19" pageNumber="245">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
, and from 
<collectingCountry box="[988,1074,331,357]" name="Mexico" pageId="19" pageNumber="245">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[1108,1203,331,357]" name="Ecuador" pageId="19" pageNumber="245">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, with several gaps in Central America (
<bibRefCitation author="Pacheco-Chaves, B. &amp; Cordeiro, I. R. S. &amp; Moreira, F. F. F. &amp; Springer, M." box="[350,669,367,394]" pageId="19" pageNumber="245" pagination="493 - 522" refId="ref10434" refString="Pacheco-Chaves, B., Cordeiro, I. R. S., Moreira, F. F. F. &amp; Springer, M. (2018) The water striders (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerridae) of Costa Rica: new species, checklist, and new records. Zootaxa, 4471 (3), 493 - 522. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4471.3.4" type="journal article" year="2018">
Pacheco-Chaves 
<emphasis box="[544,594,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="245">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). There is only one previous record from 
<collectingCountry box="[1133,1225,368,394]" name="Panama" pageId="19" pageNumber="245">Panama</collectingCountry>
, in the Canal Zone (
<bibRefCitation author="Drake, C. J. &amp; Harris, H. M." box="[159,402,403,429]" pageId="19" pageNumber="245" pagination="357 - 362" refId="ref8956" refString="Drake, C. J. &amp; Harris, H. M. (1937) Notes on some American Halobatinae (Gerridae, Hemiptera). Revista de Entomologia, 7, 357 - 362." type="journal article" year="1937">Drake &amp; Harris 1937</bibRefCitation>
), and we report here its occurrence in 
<collectingRegion box="[829,1005,403,429]" country="Panama" name="Colon" pageId="19" pageNumber="245">Colón Province</collectingRegion>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
